{"parse":{"title":"Freinet Modern School Movement","pageid":35570444,"revid":813270317,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/Modern_School_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Modern School (disambiguation)\">Modern School</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:FIMEM-World.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/FIMEM-World.png/400px-FIMEM-World.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"185\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/FIMEM-World.png/600px-FIMEM-World.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/FIMEM-World.png/800px-FIMEM-World.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1357\" data-file-height=\"628\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:FIMEM-World.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Countries with Modern School Movements in 2005.  Some countries noted on the map are not members of FIMEM.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Modern School Movement</b> <small>(French: <a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouvement_de_l%27%C3%89cole_Moderne\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:Mouvement de l&#39;\u00c9cole Moderne\">Mouvement de l'\u00c9cole Moderne</a>)</small> is the community of teachers who follow the educational and social practices of <a href=\"/wiki/Celestin_Freinet\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Celestin Freinet\">Celestin Freinet</a>, his wife \u00c9lise and their successors.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#In_francophone_countries\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In francophone countries</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#In_the_world\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">In the world</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Publications_of_the_Movement\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications of the Movement</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_francophone_countries\">In francophone countries</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Freinet_Modern_School_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: In francophone countries\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/wiki/France\" title=\"France\">France</a>, the Modern School Movement is represented by the Cooperative Institute of the Modern School (ICEM), which was founded in 1947 by Freinet and his regional groups.  Freinet led the movement until his death in 1966. After his death, ICEM has moved away from the ideas of Freinet, with multiple influences.\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Belgium\" title=\"Belgium\">Belgium</a> (Wallonia), there is a branch under the name <i>\u00c9ducation populaire</i> since 1937.  \nIn <a href=\"/wiki/Switzerland\" title=\"Switzerland\">Switzerland</a>, in 1998 the <i>Swiss Group of the Modern School</i> united three smaller groups: theRomand Group of the Modern School (est. 1952), the Genevan Group of the Modern School (est. 1968), and the <i>Swiss German Freinet Pedagogy Working Group</i> (German: Arbeitsgruppe P\u00e4dagogik Deutschschweiz-Freinet, est. 1977).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"In_the_world\">In the world</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Freinet_Modern_School_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: In the world\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The International Federation of Modern School Movements (FIMEM), founded in 1957, united the national movements and has organized an international congress (RIDEF) every two years.  There teachers meet to share and develop their ideas and practice.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications_of_the_Movement\">Publications of the Movement</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Freinet_Modern_School_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Publications of the Movement\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Secular Education Cooperative (CEL) was founded in 1928 to produce teaching materials for those who practiced Freinet's pedagogy, and magazines and brochures for the Movement.  It was taken over by teaches of the movement in 1986, after financial problems, and became the limited liability company French Modern School Publications (PEMF). This publishing house later moved away from publishing exclusively manuscripts for Freinet teachers, embracing the full range of education journals such as <i>The New Educator</i> or <i><a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biblioth%C3%A8que_de_travail\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:Biblioth\u00e8que de travail\">Library of Work</a></i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Freinet_Modern_School_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">From <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/19980110031614/http://freinet.org/\">Freinet.org</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Freinet_Modern_School_Movement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.freinet.org/archives/index.htm\">Archives of the Freinet Movement</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.icem-pedagogie-freinet.org/\">ICEM in France</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.freinet.org/espericem/\">ICEM-Esperanto</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://freinet.org/educpop\">\u00c9ducation populaire, Belgium</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.freinet.ch\">GSEM, Switzerland</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/19980110031614/http://freinet.org/\">FIMEM, Global</a></li></ul>\n<p><b>Publications</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://pemf.fr/\">PEMF</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2194\nCached time: 20180918213523\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.0